Madness
shared by two.

24:16.920 --> 24:18.979
- See?

24:19.020 --> 24:21.818
- One cannot be delusional

24:21.860 --> 24:23.885
if the belief in question is
accepted as ordinary

24:23.930 --> 24:26.819
by others in that person's
culture or subculture.

24:26.860 --> 24:28.259
Or family.

24:28.300 --> 24:32.566
- My dad didn't seem delusional.

24:32.600 --> 24:34.591
He was a perfectionist.

24:36.800 --> 24:39.507
- Your dad left
hardly any evidence.

24:39.540 --> 24:42.100
- Is that why
you let me come home?

24:42.140 --> 24:43.698
To find evidence?

24:43.750 --> 24:47.140
- It was one of many
considerations.

24:47.180 --> 24:49.842
- Are we gonna
re-enact the crime?

24:49.880 --> 24:52.587
You be my dad, you be my mom,

24:52.620 --> 24:56.681
and you be the man
on the phone.

24:56.720 --> 24:58.688
- Abigail, we wanted you
to come home

24:58.730 --> 25:00.789
to help you leave
home behind.

25:04.330 --> 25:06.525
- You're not gonna find
any of those girls, you know.

25:06.570 --> 25:10.529
- What makes you say that?
- He would honor every part
of them.

25:10.570 --> 25:12.800
He used to make

25:12.840 --> 25:15.877
plumbing putty
out of elk's bones.

25:15.910 --> 25:18.140
Whatever bones
are left

25:18.180 --> 25:22.310
of those girls are probably
holding pipes together.

25:22.350 --> 25:24.079
- Where did he make this putty?

25:24.120 --> 25:26.213
- At the cabin.

25:26.250 --> 25:28.218
I can show you tomorrow.

25:28.260 --> 25:30.512
- Abigail, there's
someone here.

25:33.600 --> 25:35.591
- Hey, Abigail.

25:40.030 --> 25:42.590
So, uh, does that hurt?

25:42.640 --> 25:44.699
- Sometimes.

25:46.940 --> 25:48.999
- Everybody on the block
was on the news.

25:49.040 --> 25:51.838
And everyone at school.

25:51.880 --> 25:54.314
Such whores.

25:54.350 --> 25:58.241
- Did you talk to the news?
- No. No!

25:58.290 --> 26:02.078
My mom doesn't want me talking
to you, much less the news.

26:02.120 --> 26:04.918
- Since when do you
listen to her?

26:04.960 --> 26:07.155
- Well, clearly I don't.

26:07.190 --> 26:09.294
I'm talking to you right now.

26:11.300 --> 26:14.235
Everybody thinks
you did it, you know?

26:16.640 --> 26:18.961
- Do you think I did it?

26:19.010 --> 26:22.332
- I don't think
you're the type.

26:22.380 --> 26:24.769
Then again, I didn't
think your father

26:24.810 --> 26:27.847
was the murder-suicide type.

26:27.880 --> 26:31.714
Although I guess the hunting
could have been a clue.

26:31.750 --> 26:33.718
- Mine or his?

26:33.760 --> 26:36.217
- Both, now that
you mention it.

26:36.260 --> 26:39.752
I don't think
you did it.

26:39.790 --> 26:42.350
-Ido.

26:42.400 --> 26:45.722
- This is private property.

26:45.770 --> 26:48.398
- You were the bait, right?

26:48.440 --> 26:52.206
That's how it worked? You lure
them back to Daddy for dinner?

26:52.240 --> 26:54.276
How'd you trap
my sister?

26:54.310 --> 26:57.199
Did you chat her up?
- Hey! Piss off!

26:59.210 --> 27:01.770
- Did you help your old man
cut out my sister's lungs

27:01.820 --> 27:04.641
while she was still using--

27:09.020 --> 27:12.080
(spitting)

27:12.130 --> 27:15.224
- He said he was
somebody's brother.

27:15.260 --> 27:18.969
- Marissa! Come home.

27:19.000 --> 27:20.763
- No...
- Come home!

27:20.800 --> 27:25.408
- Can you stop being
such a bitch?

27:25.440 --> 27:27.829
See you later.
- Bye.

27:38.220 --> 27:41.314
- He's gone.

27:43.360 --> 27:46.852
You've never
seen him before?

27:46.890 --> 27:48.926
- No.

27:48.960 --> 27:52.361
- Let's get back to the hotel.
We'll go to the cabin tomorrow.

27:52.400 --> 27:55.039
- We should
report this, yes?

27:55.070 --> 27:56.992
- Yes.

28:12.890 --> 28:14.949
I'm sorry, okay?

28:14.990 --> 28:16.981
This will all stop.

28:17.020 --> 28:19.056
Please. I'm gonna
make it all go away.

28:23.970 --> 28:28.293
(alarm beeping)

29:16.550 --> 29:20.213
- He cleaned everything.

29:20.250 --> 29:22.912
He said he was
afraid of germs,

29:22.960 --> 29:26.521
but I guess he was just afraid
of getting caught.

29:26.560 --> 29:30.018
- No one_else ever came
here With your dad...

29:30.060 --> 29:33.097
except you.

29:33.130 --> 29:36.793
- He made everything
by himself.

29:36.840 --> 29:40.469
Glue, butter...

29:40.510 --> 29:44.002
He sold the pelts
on Ebay or in town.

29:44.050 --> 29:47.042
He made pillows.

29:47.080 --> 29:49.412
No parts went to waste.

29:49.450 --> 29:51.816
Otherwise it was murder.

29:59.590 --> 30:02.297
He was feeding them to us.

30:02.330 --> 30:04.423
Wasn't he?

30:04.470 --> 30:07.997
- It's very likely.

30:10.870 --> 30:14.169
- Before
he cut my throat,

30:14.210 --> 30:18.078
he told me he killed those girls
so he wouldn't have to kill me.

30:18.110 --> 30:22.046
- You're not responsible for
anything your father did,
Abigail.

30:22.080 --> 30:24.514
- If he would've just killed me,

30:24.550 --> 30:27.348
none of those other girls
would be dead.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.278
- We don't know that.

30:29.320 --> 30:31.322
Your father--

30:53.180 --> 30:55.171
- I need ERT at the Hobbs cabin.

31:03.560 --> 31:06.279
- Abigail--
(screaming)

31:26.050 --> 31:29.679
- Do you think she knew the guy
down by the stream?
- Somebody's brother.

31:29.720 --> 31:31.688
- Not somebody.

31:31.720 --> 31:34.211
Abigail said he asked
if she helped her dad

31:34.260 --> 31:36.683
take his sister's lungs
While she was alive.

31:36.720 --> 31:39.086
- The young woman
on the stag head.

31:39.130 --> 31:41.291
- Cassie Boyle.

31:41.330 --> 31:44.163
Had a brother,
Nicholas.

31:44.200 --> 31:47.260
But Garrett Jacob Hobbs
didn't kill

31:47.300 --> 31:49.461
Cassie Boyle.
- I know.

31:51.470 --> 31:54.109
Garrett Jacob Hobbs would've
honored every part of her.

31:54.140 --> 31:56.700
- You brought Abigail Hobbs

31:56.740 --> 31:59.277
back to Minnesota to find out
if she was involved

31:59.310 --> 32:02.074
in her father's murders,
and another girl dies.

32:02.120 --> 32:05.248
- Yep, scraped
his knuckle on her teeth.

32:05.290 --> 32:07.679
There's foreign tissue
and what could be

32:07.720 --> 32:11.383
trace amounts of blood.
- You said that this copycat

32:11.430 --> 32:15.025
was an intelligent psychopath,
Will. That there would be
no traceable motive,

32:15.060 --> 32:17.961
no pattern. He wouldn't
kill again this way.

32:18.000 --> 32:20.161
You said it.

32:20.200 --> 32:23.089
- I may have been
wrong about that.

32:25.640 --> 32:29.098
Why would the copycat do it?
- I think he was provoked.

32:29.140 --> 32:31.301
Nicholas Boyle

32:31.350 --> 32:34.012
murdered this girl
and his own sister.

32:34.050 --> 32:38.384
- With or Without Abigail Hobbs?
- Without.

32:38.420 --> 32:40.615
- Well, do you think
that Abigail Hobbs

32:40.650 --> 32:43.050
knew Nicholas or Cassie Boyle?

32:43.090 --> 32:45.149
- No...

32:47.160 --> 32:49.219
- You don't think
she knew them...

32:49.260 --> 32:51.763
or don't want to think
that she knew them?

32:51.800 --> 32:55.031
- She said she didn't know them.

32:55.070 --> 32:57.538
(Jack sighs.)
- Dr. Bloom says that Abigail

32:57.570 --> 32:59.538
has a penchant for, uh,

32:59.570 --> 33:01.709
manipulation. Is she
manipulating you, Will?

33:01.740 --> 33:03.503
- Agent Crawford.

33:03.540 --> 33:05.474
- Look, he said he was wrong
about the copycat killer.

33:05.510 --> 33:07.705
I want to know What else
he's wrong about.

33:07.750 --> 33:09.718
- Whoever killed the girl
on the field killed this girl,

33:09.750 --> 33:12.241
I'm right about that.

33:12.290 --> 33:14.758
He knew exactly how
to mount the body.

33:14.790 --> 33:18.123
Wound patterns are almost
identical to Cassie Boyle.

33:18.160 --> 33:21.425
Same design, the same...

33:21.460 --> 33:23.724
humiliation.

33:23.760 --> 33:25.762
- Abigail Hobbs
is not a killer.

33:25.800 --> 33:29.292
But she could be
the target of one.

33:32.470 --> 33:35.337
- I think it's time that Abigail
Hobbs left home permanently.

33:35.380 --> 33:37.473
Doctor, would you be good
enough to collect Abigail

33:37.510 --> 33:39.478
and all of her belongings

33:39.510 --> 33:41.671
and escort her out
of Minnesota, please?

33:48.090 --> 33:51.184
Not you, Will.
I want you here.

33:54.700 --> 33:58.420
- (journalists):
Abigail! Abigail!

34:14.850 --> 34:18.718
- You killed my daughter!
- Abigail--

34:18.750 --> 34:20.615
- Why did you come back here?

34:20.650 --> 34:24.586
Why come back?
- Stay here. Stay here.

34:24.630 --> 34:28.350
(woman sobbing)

34:42.380 --> 34:44.348
- Abigail.

34:44.380 --> 34:47.406
- Miss Lounds.

34:47.450 --> 34:49.577
You're on the wrong side
of the police line.

34:49.620 --> 34:52.612
- I've been covering
the Minnesota Shrike long
before you got involved.

34:52.650 --> 34:55.778
I wanna help you tell
your story. You need me
now more than ever.

34:55.820 --> 34:59.278
- I wanna talk to her.
- No you don't. Go inside.

34:59.330 --> 35:02.197
- I'm not the only one lurking
about _the _Hobbs house
peeking in Windows.

35:02.230 --> 35:05.324
You really should monitor those
police lines more carefully.

35:07.400 --> 35:10.733
- Have you seen
a young man, mid-20$,

35:10.770 --> 35:13.807
ginger hair? Unwashed.

35:13.840 --> 35:15.899
- I'll tell you if I saw him

35:15.940 --> 35:18.579
if you tell me
Why it's important.

35:28.260 --> 35:31.252
(sobbing softly)

35:42.200 --> 35:45.203
_ - None of her
is gonna go to waste.

35:57.820 --> 36:01.449
(whimpering)

36:08.560 --> 36:11.290
- I'm not gonna hurt you.

36:11.330 --> 36:13.867
Okay? I just need you
to listen to me.

36:15.870 --> 36:18.703
I didn't kill
that girl, okay?

36:18.740 --> 36:20.332
I didn't kill her!

36:20.370 --> 36:21.371
Wait!

36:23.440 --> 36:25.408
Listen! I didn't--

36:45.000 --> 36:47.264
- Abigail?

36:52.640 --> 36:53.629
Abigail?

36:59.010 --> 37:00.807
- She'll be all right.

37:05.390 --> 37:07.915
Abigail.

37:07.950 --> 37:09.986
Show me what happened.

37:22.300 --> 37:25.508
- He was gonna kill me.
- Was he?

37:44.360 --> 37:47.659
This isn't self-defense,
Abigail. You butchered him.

37:47.690 --> 37:49.954
- I didn't...

37:52.330 --> 37:54.491
- They will see
What you did

37:54.540 --> 37:55.939
and they will see you

37:55.970 --> 37:58.609
as an accessory
to the crimes of your father.

38:00.610 --> 38:02.532
- I wasn't.

38:08.680 --> 38:10.318
- I can help you,

38:10.350 --> 38:12.989
if you ask me to.

38:13.020 --> 38:16.854
At great risk to
my career and my life.

38:20.130 --> 38:22.098
You have a choice.

38:22.130 --> 38:25.429
You can tell_ them
you were defending yourself

38:25.470 --> 38:29.338
when you gutted this man...

38:29.370 --> 38:31.702
or we can hide the body.

38:47.450 --> 38:50.419
- Then I don't
remember anything.

38:50.460 --> 38:53.588
Maybe a blur out of the corner
of my eye and--

38:53.630 --> 38:57.418
and then a big fat cut to black.

38:57.460 --> 39:00.964
- Well, Nicholas Boyle
attacked Abigail, you,

39:01.000 --> 39:05.107
struck Dr. Lecter
in the back of the head.

39:05.140 --> 39:08.439
- Well, Where's Abigail?
- Lecter took her back
to the hotel.

39:08.480 --> 39:10.869
- She scratched Nicholas Boyle
on his way out the back door.

39:10.910 --> 39:14.107
The blood on her hands matches
the tissue that we pulled

39:14.150 --> 39:16.072
from Marissa Schurr's mouth.

39:16.120 --> 39:19.749
- And then what, he--
he got away?

39:19.790 --> 39:21.781
- We'll catch him
one way or another.

39:24.590 --> 39:26.626
Where you going?

39:26.660 --> 39:29.128
- I wanna go home.

39:39.140 --> 39:41.131
- Hello, Abigail.

39:43.140 --> 39:47.474
- How did you know it was me?
- Hospital called.

39:49.480 --> 39:51.687
You climbed over the wall.

39:55.990 --> 39:58.049
Where else were you to go?

39:58.090 --> 40:01.059
Home is no longer an option.

40:01.090 --> 40:03.650
Come down from there.

40:20.880 --> 40:23.041
- I don't want to go to sleep.

40:23.080 --> 40:25.787
- You can't anticipate
your dreams.

40:28.050 --> 40:30.553
Can't block them,
can't repress.

40:30.590 --> 40:32.683
- I didn't honor
any part of him,

40:32.730 --> 40:35.619
so it's just murder,
isn't it?

40:35.660 --> 40:38.993
- Most would argue
self-defense.

40:39.030 --> 40:41.863
- Then why not
tell the truth?

40:41.900 --> 40:44.095
- Most would argue.
There would still be those

40:44.140 --> 40:46.131
who would say you were
taking after your father.

40:48.910 --> 40:51.777
- You're glad I killed him.

40:53.780 --> 40:55.975
- What would be the alternative?
That he killed you?

40:56.020 --> 40:57.976
- I don't know
if he was going to.

40:58.020 --> 40:59.715
- No, you don't.

41:01.720 --> 41:04.883
- You're the one
who called the house.

41:04.930 --> 41:07.819
You talked to my dad before--

41:07.860 --> 41:11.591
What did you
say to him?

41:13.600 --> 41:16.489
- A simple conversation,

41:16.540 --> 41:19.668
ascertaining if he was
home for an interview.

41:21.810 --> 41:24.779
Then why not tell the truth?

41:26.780 --> 41:30.568
- I think you called the house
as a serial killer.

41:30.620 --> 41:32.781
Just like my dad.

41:36.890 --> 41:39.654
- I am nothing like your dad.

41:39.690 --> 41:41.829
I made a mistake.

41:41.860 --> 41:44.829
Something easily misconstrued.
Not unlike yourself.

41:52.610 --> 41:54.601
I'll keep your secret.

41:56.310 --> 41:57.675
- And I'll keep yours.

42:00.580 --> 42:03.071
- No more climbing walls,
Abigail.

